    {
      "instruction": "<p>Reboil half a kettle, then dissolve the <strong>remaining beef stock mix </strong>in 250ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[450ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>with the <strong>remaining redcurrant jelly </strong>– this is your <strong>redcurrant stock</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a knob of <strong>butter </strong>over a medium heat, and once melted add 1/2 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [1 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour </strong>and cook for 1 min</p><p>Add the <strong>redcurrant stock</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>pepper</strong> then whisk until combined and cook for 3-4 min or until thickened to a gravy-like consistency – this is your <strong>redcurrant gravy</strong></p>",
